overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  application. The agent systematically navigated through the application,
  testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, report generation, PDF
  download, and admin login functionality. During this process, it identified
  that the navigation was working correctly despite initial confusion due to
  page scrolling, and confirmed that API endpoints and form validation were
  robust. The agent also noted minor issues such as ESLint warnings and an
  outdated page title. Following the testing, the agent proceeded to implement a
  series of fixes and enhancements, including updating the page title, adding
  new fields for pain and chronic fatigue screening, enhancing the mental health
  section, overhauling the sleep health analysis report, updating PDF
  generation, adding mock data, and improving the CSV export. All changes were
  committed in a structured, atomic manner using conventional commit messages.
